blog.name: inikavulpixelreviews
blog.title: Let's Talk About Pokemon!
blog.description:
Reviewing my personal opinion on every single Pokemon! Yes, all 809 of them!
(Mostly) Daily Uploads, 3 PM EST.

title: Let’s Talk About Pokemon - Sigilyph
body:
561: Sigilyph

Now here is an absolutely wondrously weird critter. One the same day the Japanese versions of Black and White released, the internet of course flooded with the leaks of what all the new Pokemon looked like. I distinctly remember Sigilyph being a Pokemon that stood out to me a lot when I saw them all for the first time. It was so bizarre looking and weirdly fascinating looking. Its body seemingly decorated like a totem, Sigilyph is about the weirdest of all “bird” Pokemon out there. It has the silhouette of a bird, but that’s about all it has in common with birds. Even the head is just a single stalk with an cycloptic eyeball on it. Still not sure if the two eyes on the mid-section are meant to be fake eyes or two extra eyes. They don’t blink on the model, so.

Sigilyph is another Pokemon to take more than just the US into account for basing this region on it, taking the South American Nazca Lines and transferring them rather literally into a Pokemon. It’s such a fun detail that the Pokedex classifies it as an “avianoid” Pokemon. Implying that it is something that only appears bird-like, but definitely isn’t a bird. The Pokedex also implies they’re man-made, saying they’re guardians of a long-lost city that is no longer standing. But regardless, they still patrol the same flight paths for years and years.

It’s just so bizarre and unlike any other Pokemon. And I love it when Pokemon get to stand out like that. And it’s not half-bad to use one either! I just haven’t used one yet. FOR SHAME, ME.

Personal Score: 10/10

I will accept all birds! Big birds! Small birds! Fake birds!

[Archive]
